proxs3 (0.7.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Fix data loss in cache.Link when source path matches the canonical cache
    path (regression hit on /v1/upload of files already living in cache):
    the copy fallback would os.Create the destination before reading from
    the source, truncating the file to zero bytes; the watcher would then
    upload the now-empty file to S3, clobbering the just-uploaded copy.
  * Fix cache self-eviction loop: a single file larger than cache_max_mb
    was deleted moments after being downloaded, which made PVE restores of
    multi-GB backups loop forever (download -> evict -> retry). Files
    modified within the last 30 minutes are now exempt from size-based
    eviction; a warning is logged when the cache stays over budget.
  * Fix PVE restore "connection error timeout" in the UI: path() no longer
    triggers a synchronous download from the API thread for content types
    where activate_volume is called (backup, iso, vztmpl, images). PVE's
    worker task handles the fetch via activate_volume where there is no
    pveproxy timeout. Snippets and import keep the prior behavior.
  * Switch /v1/download to AWS SDK manager.Downloader (4 x 64MB chunks,
    parallel Range GETs with per-chunk retry) — large-object downloads
    now survive transient network failures instead of restarting from
    zero. Symmetric with the existing manager.Uploader path.
  * Add explicit S3 HTTP transport timeouts (DialContext 30s, TLS 15s,
    ResponseHeader 60s) — fast-fail on connection problems while keeping
    body transfers unbounded.
  * Download via .downloads/<storage>/ tmp tree (sibling of the storage
    cache, outside the watcher's view), then atomic rename into place.
    Stops the watcher from ever seeing partial files.
  * Log download progress every 30 seconds with throughput so long
    transfers leave a useful trail in journalctl.
  * Bump HEAD timeout in /v1/download from 10s to 60s to handle slow S3
    regions without spurious "S3 unreachable" warnings.
  * Add `proxs3d --resync STORAGE` (with optional --force-latest): walks
    the local cache for one storage and uploads anything missing in S3
    or where the local copy is newer than the remote object. Streams
    progress to stdout; talks to the running daemon over the Unix socket.
  * Report the running PVE storage API version from api() instead of a
    hardcoded 13. PVE 9.2 is APIVER 14, so the old value triggered an
    "implementing an older storage API" warning on every plugin load and
    would have hard-failed once APIVER-APIAGE rose above 13. api() now
    returns the live APIVER when it falls within the validated 11..14 range
    (clamping to 14 otherwise), so the plugin tracks PVE forward without
    code changes. No new methods required: APIVER 14 adds only the optional
    get_identity() (N/A for an object store) and 13's activate_volume $hints
    arg is already accepted.

 -- Dave Kempe <dave@sol1.com.au>  Fri, 08 May 2026 11:00:00 +1000

